FINDING (HRD-132): a SHARED-key 12-way concurrent replay flood triggers a REAL
  data race at runner.go:132 (rc.CachedRcpt.WasReplay mutates a *Receipt the
  Receipt-caching events_processed store hands to every concurrent replay). This
  test uses PER-WORKER keys (production-faithful: real PG does NOT cache the
  Receipt today — HRD-125 precedent) so the HTTP-surface degrade contract is
  proven race-free; the shared-cached-Receipt race is OWNED by HRD-132 and proven
  at the runner layer (HRD-125). Dispatch exactly-once is NOT guaranteed under
  concurrent replay (HRD-132); events_processed archival IS exactly-once. The
  nil-Redis PG-only fallback idempotency is proven at HRD-125 nil_redis_degrade.txt.
